"script": "That yellow gunk in your ear isn't dirt, and it definitely isn't waste. You see, glands deep in your ear canal constantly ooze a sticky oil that mixes with dead skin cells to form earwax. And this gloop is doing a serious job. It traps dust, bacteria, and even tiny insects before they can crawl toward your fragile eardrum. It's also slightly acidic, which kills germs on contact. Then, as your jaw moves while you chew and talk, the old wax slowly migrates out of your ear, carrying the trapped junk with it. So your ear is basically self-cleaning flypaper.",
